## Bugs and notes

- Slow test: filer=BS_U_Low,Pool He is very slow but only if BSplineOrthogonality runs first.  BSplineOrthogonality fills
  DBCache with nothing other than a lot of Overlap matricies.  gprof thinks both cases are identical!!
  Need a real profiler to figure this out.
  For now we scrub the cache after the BasisSetPoolTests/XXXOrthogonality tests.
  Another hint.  THis only showed up when add one more grid point to Bspline RadialType ?!?
  Maybe we need valgrind???
  UPDATE (2026-06-20): an ASan build is now set up at `build/ASan` (clang -fsanitize=address). Run
  `ASAN_OPTIONS=detect_leaks=1 build/ASan/UnitTests/UTMain --gtest_filter=...`. Faster than valgrind
  for this codebase and catches stack/global overflows too (but NOT uninitialized reads -> valgrind).

- DFT fit-basis leak (found via ASan 2026-06-20): the DFT Hamiltonian builds a CD fit basis
  (`BasisSet::CreateCDFitBasisSet` -> `EFit_IBS`) that is never freed -- LSan shows the fit-basis
  radials leaking on water_DFT (old PG ~1.6MB / 21k allocs, new PG1 ~0.6MB). The HF path is
  leak-clean. Pre-existing in BOTH trees (shared Hamiltonian/fit-basis ownership), not the PG
  refactor. Fix: pin down who owns the result of CreateCDFitBasisSet and ensure ~Ham_DFT_U (or the
  SCFIterator) deletes it.


